boxly.Rmd
library(boxly)
meta <- meta_boxly()
meta
#> ADaM metadata: 
#>    .$data_population     Population data with 254 subjects 
#>    .$data_observation    Observation data with 24746 records 
#>    .$plan    Analysis plan with 2 plans 
#> 
#> 
#>   Analysis population type:
#>     name        id  group var       subset                         label
#> 1 'apat' 'USUBJID' 'TRTA'     SAFFL == 'Y' 'All Participants as Treated'
#> 
#> 
#>   Analysis observation type:
#>     name        id  group     var
#> 1 'wk12' 'USUBJID' 'TRTA' 'PARAM'
#> 2 'wk24' 'USUBJID' 'TRTA' 'PARAM'
#>                                                        subset            label
#> 1                ANL01FL == 'Y' & AVISITN <= 12 & !is.na(CHG)  'Weeks 0 to 12'
#> 2 ANL01FL == 'Y' & AVISITN > 12 & AVISITN <= 24 & !is.na(CHG) 'Weeks 12 to 24'
#> 
#> 
#>   Analysis parameter type:
#>       name                label              subset
#> 1 'sodium'    'Sodium (mmol/L)' PARAMCD == 'SODIUM'
#> 2   'bili' 'Bilirubin (umol/L)'   PARAMCD == 'BILI'
#> 3  'urate'     'Urate (umol/L)'  PARAMCD == 'URATE'
#> 
#> 
#>   Analysis function:
#>         name                                          label
#> 1 'lb_boxly' 'Interactive: box plot for laboratory results'
outdata <- prepare_boxly(meta,
  population = "apat",
  observation = "wk12",
  parameter = "sodium;bili;urate",
  analysis = "lb_boxly"
)
tmp1 <- outdata |> boxly()
tmp1
